WorldStage Newsonline– With the planned acquisition of an additional 10 megahertz (MHz) spectrum in the 900 MHz band in Nigeria from  Intercellular Nigeria Limited  at $70 million,  Airtel Africa Plc  is set to expand its telecommunications network across Nigeria . Commenting on the acquisition, Raghunath Mandava, the Chief Executive of Airtel Africa, said that data was the key pillar of the company’s growth. Mandava said that it was also driven by increasing 4G networks, supported by the increased affordability and increasing penetration of smartphones. He explained that data presents a significant opportunity for growth with an overall smartphone penetration of more than 35 per cent and data consumption growing by 92 per cent in the six months period ended Sept. 30. Airtel Africa stated  that the acquisition was subject to regulatory approval by the Nigerian Communication (NCC).